    {
      "line": 59,
      "text": "drawings by R. Crumb"
    },
    {
      "line": 62,
      "text": "Only 1 in every 100 people on this planet has a sufficiently"
    },
    {
      "line": 63,
      "text": "solid democratic culture that he or she can feel secure about"
    },
    {
      "line": 64,
      "text": "attempting to transmit it to other environments."
    },
    {
      "line": 67,
      "text": "The United States does not qualify as such a democracy."
    },
    {
      "line": 70,
      "text": "No stranger to the character of democracy, public advocate Bob Gnaizda conducted a 1965 congressional hearing in"
    },
    {
      "line": 71,
      "text": "Mississippi to investigate why no blacks voted in black-majority Clay County. Answer: because our country was not"
    },
    {
      "line": 72,
      "text": "what we claimed to be. Bob Gnaizda later argued that we could use a little realism where democracy hits our checkbooks"
    },
    {
      "line": 73,
      "text": "in “The Simple Tax: Common Sense Government” for CQ #38. The San Jose Mercury News first printed this scrutiny"
    },
    {
      "line": 74,
      "text": "of democracy last year July 1. -Kevin Kelly"
